%N A396235 Irregular triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of length n almost topological sequences of three dimensional lattice points with index k.
%C A396235 Here the lexicographic well-ordering (i,j,k) < (x,y,z) and the partial order (i,j,k) <* (x,y,z) if i <= x, j <= y, and k <= z are used. An almost topological sequence (ATS) S of length n, S = (x_1, x_2, ..., x_n) is an ordered collection of elements such that for all b in S if a <* b then a is a element of S and appears before b. The index of an ATS is the sum of the indices of elements x_i of S such that x_i > x_{i+1}.
%C A396235 Row n is also the numerator coefficients of the generating function for the number of solid partitions with exactly n parts.
%H A396235 Wouter Meeussen, <a href="/A396235/b396235.txt">Rows n = 0..26</a> (Rows n = 0..10 from John Tyler Rascoe).
%H A396235 Wouter Meeussen, <a href="/A396235/a396235.pdf">Alternative calculation technique</a>
%H A396235 John Tyler Rascoe, <a href="/A396235/a396235.txt">PARI code</a>.
%e A396235 Triangle begins:
%e A396235      k=0  1   2   3   4  5   6  7
%e A396235  n=0   1;
%e A396235  n=1   1;
%e A396235  n=2   3;
%e A396235  n=3   6, 0,  3;
%e A396235  n=4  13, 0, 11,  8,  0, 1;
%e A396235  n=5  24, 0, 27, 33, 24, 6, 18, 3;
%e A396235  ...
%e A396235 The ATS of length 3: ((0,0,0), (0,1,0), (0,0,1)) has an index of 2 since (0,1,0) > (0,0,1), so this ATS is counted under T(3,2) = 3.
